HEADWORD: Meliaceous
<hw>Me`li*a"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to a natural order (<ord>Meliacae</ord>) of plants of
which the genus <gen>Melia</gen> is the type. It includes the mahogany
and the Spanish cedar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

